ng of cool gas near the blob outskirts\nshapes the observed blue-dominated Ly$\\alpha$ profiles, but its energy\ncontribution to the total Ly$\\alpha$ luminosity is less than 10%, i.e. minor\ncompared to the photo-ionization by star-forming galaxies and/or AGNs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Apr 2021 17:59:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Apr 2022 00:30:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-20"}
